1. get moving. whether it'ms a dance party, a walk around the block, or a quickie workout, getting your body moving can help release endorphins and improve your mood.

2. call a friend or family member. sometimes all we need is someone to listen and make us feel loved and supported.

3. do something creative. whether it's painting, drawing, writing, or playing music, making something can be a great way to express yourself and take your mind off your troubles.

4. get outside. being in nature can be a great mood booster. even if it's just a walk around the block or a few minutes of sitting in the park, being outside can help you feel more connected to the world around you.

5. do something you love. whether it's reading a book, watching a movie, or playing a game, taking time to do something you enjoy can help distract you from your feelings and improve your mood.

